gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Nuggets 130, Cavaliers 101
gameRecap.excerpt: The Nuggets hit a season-high 21 3PT FGs as they defeated the Cavaliers, 130-101, improve to 52-23 on the year, and clinch a playoff spot. Nikola Jokic led Denver with 26 points, 18 rebounds, and 16 assists as Kentavious Caldwell-Pope went for 22 points and a season-high six 3PM. Evan Mobley led Cleveland with 23 points and four rebounds as they moved to 45-30.
